1
00:00:00,120 --> 00:00:00,960
This is Bill.

2
00:00:00,960 --> 00:00:04,650
Every morning, he wakes up to
the sound of a piercing alarm,

3
00:00:04,650 --> 00:00:07,980
dreading the day ahead
at a job he despises.

4
00:00:07,980 --> 00:00:10,320
He feels trapped, undervalued,

5
00:00:10,320 --> 00:00:13,080
and like he's not making
any progress in life.

6
00:00:13,080 --> 00:00:14,880
Bill comes to the conclusion

7
00:00:14,880 --> 00:00:17,070
that the only way out his situation

8
00:00:17,070 --> 00:00:20,220
is to start a business
and become his own boss,

9
00:00:20,220 --> 00:00:22,650
so he quits his job and goes for it.

10
00:00:22,650 --> 00:00:25,410
Now I'm sure you want this
story to have a happy ending.

11
00:00:25,410 --> 00:00:27,960
However, life doesn't
really work like that.

12
00:00:27,960 --> 00:00:29,790
As a multi-millionaire businessman,

13
00:00:29,790 --> 00:00:32,340
I've seen hundreds of
people who quit their jobs

14
00:00:32,340 --> 00:00:34,020
and start their own businesses,

15
00:00:34,020 --> 00:00:36,510
and only a small percentage of them

16
00:00:36,510 --> 00:00:37,980
end up being successful.

17
00:00:37,980 --> 00:00:40,740
That's because, and I'm
not gonna sugarcoat it,

18
00:00:40,740 --> 00:00:44,100
most people don't have what it
takes to be an entrepreneur.

19
00:00:44,100 --> 00:00:46,110
Before you think I'm trying
to crush your dreams,

20
00:00:46,110 --> 00:00:48,300
I'm not, I'm just saying it how it is.

21
00:00:48,300 --> 00:00:51,660
So before you think about
starting any kind of business,

22
00:00:51,660 --> 00:00:54,510
make sure you take the
following five steps.

23
00:00:54,510 --> 00:00:57,180
Step one, kill your delusion.

24
00:00:57,180 --> 00:00:58,620
You've been fed the lie

25
00:00:58,620 --> 00:01:00,630
that becoming a successful entrepreneur

26
00:01:00,630 --> 00:01:03,210
is all about coming up
with the perfect idea.

27
00:01:03,210 --> 00:01:04,350
They want you to believe

28
00:01:04,350 --> 00:01:06,330
that the only thing
that stands in your way

29
00:01:06,330 --> 00:01:08,070
is that light bulb moment,

30
00:01:08,070 --> 00:01:10,830
and once you have it,
everything will go perfectly.

31
00:01:10,830 --> 00:01:14,370
That's because selling this
delusion is highly profitable.

32
00:01:14,370 --> 00:01:16,200
I mean, I'm sure you've
seen the headlines,

33
00:01:16,200 --> 00:01:19,410
like, "How I Built a Million-Dollar
Business in 30 Days,"

34
00:01:19,410 --> 00:01:22,800
or, "How I Fired My Boss and
Started My Own Business."

35
00:01:22,800 --> 00:01:24,750
These stories might be true

36
00:01:24,750 --> 00:01:26,700
but they're very out of the ordinary

37
00:01:26,700 --> 00:01:29,730
and they don't take into account
all the previous failures

38
00:01:29,730 --> 00:01:31,500
that that person had to go through

39
00:01:31,500 --> 00:01:33,120
to get to where they are today.

40
00:01:33,120 --> 00:01:35,580
Media outlets and social media gurus

41
00:01:35,580 --> 00:01:36,990
make things sound easy

42
00:01:36,990 --> 00:01:39,870
so they can capitalize off your delusion.

43
00:01:39,870 --> 00:01:42,180
But guess what, you're being lied to.

44
00:01:42,180 --> 00:01:44,520
In order to become successful in business,

45
00:01:44,520 --> 00:01:46,800
you need to burst this bubble of lies.

46
00:01:46,800 --> 00:01:48,900
Otherwise, it will be burst for you,

47
00:01:48,900 --> 00:01:51,600
and trust me, this is way more damaging.

48
00:01:51,600 --> 00:01:55,050
For me, this harsh reality
check happened very early on.

49
00:01:55,050 --> 00:01:57,060
I shared my business plans with a friend

50
00:01:57,060 --> 00:01:58,860
and he stole all my ideas

51
00:01:58,860 --> 00:02:00,720
and set up a business for himself.

52
00:02:00,720 --> 00:02:02,760
Fortunately, I didn't have many options,

53
00:02:02,760 --> 00:02:04,920
like a fancy degree to fall back on,

54
00:02:04,920 --> 00:02:06,990
so I had no choice but to adapt

55
00:02:06,990 --> 00:02:08,880
and come up with a new strategy.

56
00:02:08,880 --> 00:02:10,200
I suppose that's the difference

57
00:02:10,200 --> 00:02:13,440
between wanting it to
work and needing it to.

58
00:02:13,440 --> 00:02:15,390
When you're left with no other options,

59
00:02:15,390 --> 00:02:17,520
you're much more likely
to come out on top.

60
00:02:17,520 --> 00:02:19,560
I see way too many people giving up

61
00:02:19,560 --> 00:02:21,750
when they hit that first big challenge

62
00:02:21,750 --> 00:02:24,840
as they can't understand why
it's not working out perfectly

63
00:02:24,840 --> 00:02:26,250
like they were led to believe.

64
00:02:26,250 --> 00:02:27,840
But I've got some news for you.

65
00:02:27,840 --> 00:02:30,210
Successful people aren't business gods

66
00:02:30,210 --> 00:02:32,340
who get it right every time.

67
00:02:32,340 --> 00:02:34,470
Most entrepreneurs are winging it.

68
00:02:34,470 --> 00:02:36,540
They've never got all of the answers.

69
00:02:36,540 --> 00:02:38,250
I mean, the majority of businesses

70
00:02:38,250 --> 00:02:40,740
on "Shark Tan" and "Dragons' Den"

71
00:02:40,740 --> 00:02:43,290
they fail and they've got
billionaires backing them.

72
00:02:43,290 --> 00:02:44,580
Your biggest heroes

73
00:02:44,580 --> 00:02:46,890
have probably faced more
struggles than most,

74
00:02:46,890 --> 00:02:49,650
but that's the reason
you're inspired by them.

75
00:02:49,650 --> 00:02:51,000
After every setback,

76
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:52,500
they pulled themselves together

77
00:02:52,500 --> 00:02:54,810
and came back bigger
and better than before.

78
00:02:54,810 --> 00:02:57,750
So kill your delusion, expect failure,

79
00:02:57,750 --> 00:03:00,840
and accept that success doesn't come easy.

80
00:03:00,840 --> 00:03:03,600
Step two, replace your friends.

81
00:03:03,600 --> 00:03:04,830
In my early 20s,

82
00:03:04,830 --> 00:03:08,520
I spent every waking hour
building my first business.

83
00:03:08,520 --> 00:03:10,890
I was so obsessed that
I didn't even notice

84
00:03:10,890 --> 00:03:12,420
how lonely I was deep down.

85
00:03:12,420 --> 00:03:14,580
A recent national survey by Cigna

86
00:03:14,580 --> 00:03:17,160
actually showed that
almost half of Americans

87
00:03:17,160 --> 00:03:18,627
report feeling lonely,

88
00:03:18,627 --> 00:03:21,960
and I suspect this is much
higher for entrepreneurs.

89
00:03:21,960 --> 00:03:23,970
I worked so hard for so long

90
00:03:23,970 --> 00:03:25,920
and when I finally came up for air

91
00:03:25,920 --> 00:03:28,800
I realized I'd lost almost all my friends

92
00:03:28,800 --> 00:03:30,570
and the friends that I still had

93
00:03:30,570 --> 00:03:32,700
could no longer relate to my mindset,

94
00:03:32,700 --> 00:03:34,350
lifestyle or struggles.

95
00:03:34,350 --> 00:03:35,640
If you're anything like me,

96
00:03:35,640 --> 00:03:38,190
then you're bound to
experience something similar,

97
00:03:38,190 --> 00:03:40,110
and the more successful you get,

98
00:03:40,110 --> 00:03:41,970
the more the disconnect will grow.

99
00:03:41,970 --> 00:03:44,460
For some time, I felt lost and alone,

100
00:03:44,460 --> 00:03:46,740
thinking that I was the problem.

101
00:03:46,740 --> 00:03:49,200
But then it hit me like a ton of bricks.

102
00:03:49,200 --> 00:03:53,100
Outgrowing old friends is a
painful yet inevitable part

103
00:03:53,100 --> 00:03:54,450
of the growth process.

104
00:03:54,450 --> 00:03:57,060
If your friends aren't
prepared to grow with you,

105
00:03:57,060 --> 00:03:59,850
then you shouldn't be wasting
your valuable time with them.

106
00:03:59,850 --> 00:04:02,490
Now it's the time to seek out new people

107
00:04:02,490 --> 00:04:04,770
who are willing to level up alongside you.

108
00:04:04,770 --> 00:04:07,830
That's why it can be a great
idea to have a co-founder,

109
00:04:07,830 --> 00:04:09,750
as they're in the trenches with you

110
00:04:09,750 --> 00:04:11,640
and you're able to motivate each other

111
00:04:11,640 --> 00:04:12,780
when you're feeling down.

112
00:04:12,780 --> 00:04:15,000
Just be careful when you're
selecting your co-founder

113
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:17,640
because this is the person
you're gonna be spending

114
00:04:17,640 --> 00:04:20,070
a significant amount of time with,

115
00:04:20,070 --> 00:04:21,450
even more than your family,

116
00:04:21,450 --> 00:04:23,580
so it's very important that you know

117
00:04:23,580 --> 00:04:26,070
how this person reacts
through tough times.

118
00:04:26,070 --> 00:04:28,230
It's also a good idea to join communities

119
00:04:28,230 --> 00:04:29,970
full of other entrepreneurs.

120
00:04:29,970 --> 00:04:32,400
I run one of the biggest
free Discord servers

121
00:04:32,400 --> 00:04:33,810
called "Strike It Big"

122
00:04:33,810 --> 00:04:35,340
and you're very welcome to join.

123
00:04:35,340 --> 00:04:37,590
There's about 30,000
entrepreneurs in there

124
00:04:37,590 --> 00:04:40,830
discussing all things
business and making money.

125
00:04:40,830 --> 00:04:42,840
I'll leave a link in
the description below,

126
00:04:42,840 --> 00:04:44,220
it's completely free.

127
00:04:44,220 --> 00:04:47,820
So, replace your friends,
find like-minded people,

128
00:04:47,820 --> 00:04:49,260
and never look back.

129
00:04:49,260 --> 00:04:51,570
Step three, rethink money.

130
00:04:51,570 --> 00:04:53,670
My friend Daniel
Priestley used to struggle

131
00:04:53,670 --> 00:04:56,910
with closing high-value deals
in his job as a salesman.

132
00:04:56,910 --> 00:04:59,190
The truth is he felt uncomfortable

133
00:04:59,190 --> 00:05:01,110
asking for large sums of money

134
00:05:01,110 --> 00:05:03,630
because he placed too
much value on it himself.

135
00:05:03,630 --> 00:05:06,120
Potential customers could
sense his awkwardness

136
00:05:06,120 --> 00:05:07,500
when discussing money,

137
00:05:07,500 --> 00:05:09,720
which would often lead
to him losing a deal

138
00:05:09,720 --> 00:05:11,010
at the final hurdle.

139
00:05:11,010 --> 00:05:13,080
That's when his mentor had to step in.

140
00:05:13,080 --> 00:05:16,740
He told him to carry $1,000
in cash in his pocket

141
00:05:16,740 --> 00:05:18,330
wherever he went.

142
00:05:18,330 --> 00:05:20,460
At first he thought this was crazy,

143
00:05:20,460 --> 00:05:21,780
but he followed the advice

144
00:05:21,780 --> 00:05:24,510
and scraped together all of
the money he had at the time.

145
00:05:24,510 --> 00:05:26,670
Because he was carrying
it around every day,

146
00:05:26,670 --> 00:05:29,160
it quickly started to feel insignificant

147
00:05:29,160 --> 00:05:31,020
and little more than pocket change.

148
00:05:31,020 --> 00:05:34,110
It completely adjusted
his attitude towards money

149
00:05:34,110 --> 00:05:37,680
and helped him become a
multi-millionaire in his early 20s.

150
00:05:37,680 --> 00:05:39,510
If you currently work a day job,

151
00:05:39,510 --> 00:05:41,280
you probably have this issue as well

152
00:05:41,280 --> 00:05:42,720
without even knowing it.

153
00:05:42,720 --> 00:05:45,120
But if you want to be
successful in business,

154
00:05:45,120 --> 00:05:46,230
then you have to believe

155
00:05:46,230 --> 00:05:49,140
that there is so much money out
there waiting to be grabbed,

156
00:05:49,140 --> 00:05:50,370
and most importantly,

157
00:05:50,370 --> 00:05:51,960
not be afraid to spend it.

158
00:05:51,960 --> 00:05:53,280
As a business owner,

159
00:05:53,280 --> 00:05:55,650
I've spent hundreds of
thousands of dollars

160
00:05:55,650 --> 00:05:57,900
this month alone without hesitation

161
00:05:57,900 --> 00:06:00,990
because I know that
investing in my business,

162
00:06:00,990 --> 00:06:04,350
whether in staff, stock, or technology,

163
00:06:04,350 --> 00:06:06,720
will have a positive
effect in the long term.

164
00:06:06,720 --> 00:06:08,670
So you need to stop thinking of money

165
00:06:08,670 --> 00:06:10,980
as a valuable asset that's hard to get

166
00:06:10,980 --> 00:06:13,800
and start viewing it as
a tool to build wealth.

167
00:06:13,800 --> 00:06:16,620
Step four, maximize efficiency.

168
00:06:16,620 --> 00:06:20,550
Did you know that 72% of
all small business owners

169
00:06:20,550 --> 00:06:22,500
struggle with feeling overwhelmed?

170
00:06:22,500 --> 00:06:24,120
It's no wonder they feel this way

171
00:06:24,120 --> 00:06:27,000
given the constant pressure
to meet daily targets,

172
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:29,490
make decisions about the
future of the business,

173
00:06:29,490 --> 00:06:30,960
and generate revenue,

174
00:06:30,960 --> 00:06:33,630
all while trying to maintain
some kind of social life.

175
00:06:33,630 --> 00:06:36,840
You just have so many plates
to spin as an entrepreneur,

176
00:06:36,840 --> 00:06:38,647
that's why when someone says to me,

177
00:06:38,647 --> 00:06:40,890
"You're the boss, you
can take the day off,"

178
00:06:40,890 --> 00:06:42,600
it really (beep) me off.

179
00:06:42,600 --> 00:06:44,280
When you work a normal job,

180
00:06:44,280 --> 00:06:46,650
you only have to focus on the day ahead.

181
00:06:46,650 --> 00:06:49,080
After work, you can go home and relax.

182
00:06:49,080 --> 00:06:51,120
However, for a business owner,

183
00:06:51,120 --> 00:06:53,520
it's very hard to ever switch off.

184
00:06:53,520 --> 00:06:55,650
You know that you're solely responsible

185
00:06:55,650 --> 00:06:57,720
for making sure the money keeps flowing,

186
00:06:57,720 --> 00:07:01,050
that's why I hate it when
people put down normal jobs.

187
00:07:01,050 --> 00:07:03,030
Not everyone wants the stress

188
00:07:03,030 --> 00:07:04,770
that comes with running a business,

189
00:07:04,770 --> 00:07:06,600
and that is completely fine.

190
00:07:06,600 --> 00:07:08,550
However, for those of you like me

191
00:07:08,550 --> 00:07:11,190
that have a burning desire to do business,

192
00:07:11,190 --> 00:07:13,980
there is a way to maximize efficiency

193
00:07:13,980 --> 00:07:15,870
and keep things running smoothly.

194
00:07:15,870 --> 00:07:17,700
The biggest thing that's helped me manage

195
00:07:17,700 --> 00:07:19,500
my stress levels over the years

196
00:07:19,500 --> 00:07:22,830
is putting in place great
systems and processes.

197
00:07:22,830 --> 00:07:25,320
This is because from my experience

198
00:07:25,320 --> 00:07:27,540
the most stress comes
from when your business

199
00:07:27,540 --> 00:07:28,950
is reliant on people.

200
00:07:28,950 --> 00:07:30,870
It's easy to get caught up in the thrill

201
00:07:30,870 --> 00:07:32,700
of starting a new business,

202
00:07:32,700 --> 00:07:34,680
but have you ever thought
about what happens

203
00:07:34,680 --> 00:07:36,150
when your business grows

204
00:07:36,150 --> 00:07:38,910
and one of your key
employees suddenly leaves?

205
00:07:38,910 --> 00:07:42,300
That's where having systems and
processes in place comes in.

206
00:07:42,300 --> 00:07:44,640
Think of it like a big
manual to your business

207
00:07:44,640 --> 00:07:46,170
that anyone can follow,

208
00:07:46,170 --> 00:07:48,960
even if they're not familiar
with your specific company.

209
00:07:48,960 --> 00:07:51,780
It's important to start
thinking about this early on

210
00:07:51,780 --> 00:07:53,700
because as your business grows

211
00:07:53,700 --> 00:07:55,320
it will become harder and harder

212
00:07:55,320 --> 00:07:56,730
to keep track of everything.

213
00:07:56,730 --> 00:07:58,560
This also has the added benefit

214
00:07:58,560 --> 00:08:00,930
of making the business far more attractive

215
00:08:00,930 --> 00:08:03,210
to potential buyers in the future

216
00:08:03,210 --> 00:08:05,070
as they know that they have a full guide

217
00:08:05,070 --> 00:08:06,690
of how to operate that business

218
00:08:06,690 --> 00:08:08,730
and get a return on their investment.

219
00:08:08,730 --> 00:08:11,790
So, think ahead, maximize efficiency,

220
00:08:11,790 --> 00:08:14,250
and get your systems
and processes in place

221
00:08:14,250 --> 00:08:15,900
before it's too late.

222
00:08:15,900 --> 00:08:18,390
Step five, become a wolf.

223
00:08:18,390 --> 00:08:20,070
If you wanna become successful,

224
00:08:20,070 --> 00:08:22,410
then you need to build some kind of team.

225
00:08:22,410 --> 00:08:23,970
If you think you can do it all alone,

226
00:08:23,970 --> 00:08:25,770
then you're solely mistaken.

227
00:08:25,770 --> 00:08:27,000
You need a pack.

228
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:28,500
Now I want you to imagine

229
00:08:28,500 --> 00:08:31,230
you have an extremely successful business

230
00:08:31,230 --> 00:08:33,390
but you're running it all by yourself.

231
00:08:33,390 --> 00:08:36,300
You're making great money
but it's coming at the cost

232
00:08:36,300 --> 00:08:38,850
of your relationships and experiences,

233
00:08:38,850 --> 00:08:42,720
so you decide it's time to
hire your first employee.

234
00:08:42,720 --> 00:08:43,710
I know this might seem

235
00:08:43,710 --> 00:08:45,780
like a million miles away at the moment,

236
00:08:45,780 --> 00:08:46,890
but stick with me.

237
00:08:46,890 --> 00:08:48,840
Just imagine all the little tasks

238
00:08:48,840 --> 00:08:50,190
you could take off your plate

239
00:08:50,190 --> 00:08:52,620
and give to someone else to take care of.

240
00:08:52,620 --> 00:08:55,410
Just the thought of that
seems pretty exciting,

241
00:08:55,410 --> 00:08:56,640
but at the same time

242
00:08:56,640 --> 00:08:59,760
it comes with a lot of challenges
and potential mistakes.

243
00:08:59,760 --> 00:09:01,860
I remember hiring my first employee

244
00:09:01,860 --> 00:09:03,660
to serve customers in my shop.

245
00:09:03,660 --> 00:09:06,390
It was such a relief to have
someone there to help me.

246
00:09:06,390 --> 00:09:10,410
If I asked you to describe
exactly what kind of employee

247
00:09:10,410 --> 00:09:12,240
you would want in the future,

248
00:09:12,240 --> 00:09:13,860
then you'd probably outline someone

249
00:09:13,860 --> 00:09:15,900
that is very similar to yourself,

250
00:09:15,900 --> 00:09:18,870
but this is completely
wrong way of looking at it.

251
00:09:18,870 --> 00:09:21,480
The truth is you're
never gonna find someone

252
00:09:21,480 --> 00:09:22,920
exactly like you,

253
00:09:22,920 --> 00:09:24,120
because if they were,

254
00:09:24,120 --> 00:09:26,460
then they'd be running
a competing business.

255
00:09:26,460 --> 00:09:27,900
The key is to hire people

256
00:09:27,900 --> 00:09:30,450
who are better than
you in different areas.

257
00:09:30,450 --> 00:09:33,120
This way they don't just
do what you would do,

258
00:09:33,120 --> 00:09:36,330
they actually level up your
business by doing it better.

259
00:09:36,330 --> 00:09:39,660
So pick the members of your
wolf pack strategically

260
00:09:39,660 --> 00:09:42,120
and share your success
with them along the way.

261
00:09:42,120 --> 00:09:44,670
Look, starting a business
is not for everyone,

262
00:09:44,670 --> 00:09:47,010
but quitting my job
and starting a business

263
